    24→## mdBook 0.5.1
    25→[v0.5.0...v0.5.1](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/v0.5.0...v0.5.1)
    27→### Changed
    28→- Changed the scrollbar background to be transparent.
    29→  [#2932](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2932)
    30→- Ignore invalid top-level environment variable config keys. This allows setting things like `MDBOOK_VERSION` to not cause an error.
    31→  [#2952](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2952)
    33→### Fixed
    34→- Fixed the sidebar heading nav to have the correct nesting levels.
    35→  [#2953](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2953)
    36→- Various Font Awesome fixes and improvements.
    37→  [#2951](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2951)
    39→## mdBook 0.5.0
    40→[v0.4.52...v0.5.0](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/v0.4.52...v0.5.0)
    53→## 0.5 Migration Guide
    54→
    55→The 0.5 release contains several breaking changes from the 0.4 release. Preprocessors and renderers will need to be migrated to continue to work with this release. After updating your configuration, it is recommended to carefully compare and review how your book renders to ensure everything is working correctly.
    63→### Major additions
    64→
    65→- Added sidebar heading navigation. This includes the `output.html.sidebar-header-nav` option to disable it.
    66→  [#2822](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2822)
    67→- Added support for definition lists. These are enabled by default, with the option `output.html.definition-lists` to disable it. See [docs](https://rust-lang.github.io/mdBook/format/markdown.html#definition-lists) for more.
    68→  [#2847](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2847)
    69→- Added support for admonitions. These are enabled by default, with the option `output.html.admonitions` to disable it. See [docs](https://rust-lang.github.io/mdBook/format/markdown.html#admonitions) for more.
    70→  [#2851](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2851)
    71→- Links on the print page now link to elements on the print page instead of linking out to the individual chapters.
    72→  [#2844](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2844)
    74→### Config changes
    75→
    76→- Unknown fields in config are now an error.
    77→  [#2787](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2787)
    78→  [#2801](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2801)
    79→- Removed `curly-quotes`, use `output.html.smart-punctuation` instead.
    80→  [#2788](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2788)
    81→- Removed `output.html.copy-fonts`. The default fonts are now always copied unless you override the `theme/fonts/fonts.css` file.
    82→  [#2790](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2790)
    83→- If the `command` path for a renderer or preprocessor is relative, it is now always relative to the book root.
    84→  [#2792](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2792)
    85→  [#2796](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2796)
    86→- Added the `optional` field for preprocessors. The default is `false`, so this also means it is an error by default if the preprocessor is missing.
    87→  [#2797](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2797)
    88→- `output.html.smart-punctuation` is now `true` by default.
    89→  [#2810](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2810)
    90→- `output.html.hash-files` is now `true` by default.
    91→  [#2820](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2820)
    92→- Removed support for google-analytics. Use a theme extension (like `head.hbs`) if you need to continue to support this.
    93→  [#2776](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2776)
    94→- Removed the `book.multilingual` field. This was never used.
    95→  [#2775](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2775)
    96→- Removed the very old legacy config support. Warnings have been displayed in previous versions on how to migrate.
    97→  [#2783](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2783)
    98→- Top-level config values set from the environment like `MDBOOK_BOOK` now *replace* the contents of the top-level table instead of merging into it.
    99→  [#2942](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2942)
   100→- Invalid environment variables are now rejected. Previously unknown keys like `MDBOOK_FOO` would be ignored, or keys or invalid values inside objects like the `[book]` table would be ignored.
   101→  [#2942](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2942)
   103→### Theme changes
   104→
   105→- Replaced the `{{#previous}}` and `{{#next}}` handlebars helpers with simple objects that contain the previous and next values.
   106→  [#2794](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2794)
   107→- Removed the `{{theme_option}}` handlebars helper. It has not been used for a while.
   108→  [#2795](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2795)
   110→### Rendering changes
   111→
   112→- Updated to a newer version of `pulldown-cmark`. This brings a large number of fixes to markdown processing.
   113→  [#2401](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2401)
   114→- The font-awesome font is no longer loaded as a font. Instead, the corresponding SVG is embedded in the output for the corresponding `<i>` tags. Additionally, a handlebars helper has been added for the `hbs` files. This also updates the version from 4.7.0 to 6.2.0, which means some of the icon names and styles have changed. Most of the free icons are in the "solid" set. See the [free icon set](https://fontawesome.com/v6/search) for the available icons.
   115→  [#1330](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1330)
   116→- Changed all internal HTML IDs to have an `mdbook-` prefix. This helps avoid namespace conflicts with header IDs.
   117→  [#2808](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2808)
   118→- There is a new internal HTML rendering pipeline. This is primarily intended to give mdBook more flexibility in generating its HTML output. This resulted in some small changes to the HTML structure. HTML parsing may now be more strict than before.
   119→  [#2844](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2844)
   120→- Links on the print page now link to elements on the print page instead of linking out to the individual chapters.
   121→  [#2844](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2844)
   122→- Added support for definition lists. These are enabled by default, with the option `output.html.definition-lists` to disable it.
   123→  [#2847](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2847)
   124→- Added support for admonitions. These are enabled by default, with the option `output.html.admonitions` to disable it.
   125→  [#2851](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2851)
   126→- Header ID generation has some minor changes to bring the ID generation closer to other tools and sites:
   127→  - IDs now use Unicode lowercase instead of ASCII lowercase.
   128→    [#2922](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2922)
   129→  - Headers that start or end with HTML characters like `<`, `&`, or `>` now replace those characters in the link ID with `-` instead of being stripped.
   130→    [#2844](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2844)
   131→- Headers are no longer modified if the tag is manually written HTML.
   132→  [#2913](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2913)
   134→### CLI changes
   135→
   136→- Removed the `--dest-dir` option to `mdbook test`. It was unused since `mdbook test` does not generate output.
   137→  [#2805](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2805)
   138→- Changed CLI `--dest-dir` to be relative to the current directory, not the book root.
   139→  [#2806](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2806)
   141→### Rust API
   142→
   143→- The Rust API has been split into several crates ([#2766](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2766)). In summary, the different crates are:
   144→  - `mdbook` — The CLI binary.
   145→  - [`mdbook-driver`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-driver/latest/mdbook_driver/) — The high-level library for running mdBook, primarily through the `MDBook` type. If you are driving mdBook programmatically, this is the crate you want.
   146→  - [`mdbook-preprocessor`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-preprocessor/latest/mdbook_preprocessor/) — Support for implementing preprocessors. If you have a preprocessor, then this is the crate you should depend on.
   147→  - [`mdbook-renderer`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-renderer/latest/mdbook_renderer/) — Support for implementing renderers. If you have a custom renderer, this is the crate you should depend on.
   148→  - [`mdbook-markdown`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-markdown/latest/mdbook_markdown/) — The Markdown renderer. If you are processing markdown, this is the crate you should depend on. This is essentially a thin wrapper around `pulldown-cmark`, and re-exports that crate so that you can ensure the version stays in sync with mdBook.
   149→  - [`mdbook-summary`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-summary/latest/mdbook_summary/) — The `SUMMARY.md` parser.
   150→  - [`mdbook-html`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-html/latest/mdbook_html/) — The HTML renderer.
   151→  - [`mdbook-core`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-core/latest/mdbook_core/) — An internal library that is used by the other crates for shared types. You should not depend on this crate directly since types from this crate are re-exported from the other crates as appropriate.
   152→- Changes to `Config`:
   153→  - [`Config::get`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-core/latest/mdbook_core/config/struct.Config.html#method.get) is now generic over the return value, using `serde` to deserialize the value. It also returns a `Result` to handle deserialization errors. [#2773](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2773)
   154→  - [`Config::set`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-core/latest/mdbook_core/config/struct.Config.html#method.set) now validates that the config keys and values are valid.
   155→    [#2942](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2942)
   156→  - [`Config::update_from_env`](https://docs.rs/mdbook-core/latest/mdbook_core/config/struct.Config.html#method.update_from_env) now returns a `Result` to indicate any errors.
   157→    [#2942](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2942)
   158→  - Removed `Config::get_deserialized`. Use `Config::get` instead.
   159→  - Removed `Config::get_deserialized_opt`. Use `Config::get` instead.
   160→  - Removed `Config::get_mut`. Use `Config::set` instead.
   161→  - Removed deprecated `Config::get_deserialized_opt`. Use `Config::get` instead.
   162→  - Removed `Config::get_renderer`. Use `Config::get` instead.
   163→  - Removed `Config::get_preprocessor`. Use `Config::get` instead.
   164→- Public types have been switch to use the `#[non_exhaustive]` attribute to help allow them to change in a backwards-compatible way.
   165→  [#2779](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2779)
   166→  [#2823](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2823)
   167→- Changed `MDBook` `with_renderer`/`with_preprocessor` to overwrite the entry if an extension of the same name is already loaded. This allows the caller to replace an entry.
   168→  [#2802](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2802)
   169→- Added `MarkdownOptions` struct to specify settings for markdown rendering for `mdbook_markdown::new_cmark_parser`.
   170→  [#2809](https://github.cocm/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2809)
   171→- Renamed `Book::sections` to `Book::items`.
   172→  [#2813](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2813)
   173→- `mdbook::book::load_book` is now private. Instead, use one of the `MDBook` load functions like `MDBook::load_with_config`.
   174→- Removed `HtmlConfig::smart_punctuation` method, use the field of the same name.
   175→- `CmdPreprocessor::parse_input` moved to `mdbook_preprocessor::parse_input`.
   176→- `Preprocessor::supports_renderer` now returns a `Result<bool>` instead of `bool` to be able to handle errors.
   177→- Most of the types from the `theme` module are now private. The `Theme` struct is still exposed for working with themes.
   178→- Various functions in the `utils::fs` module have been removed, renamed, or reworked.
   179→- Most of the functions in the `utils` module have been moved, removed, or made private.
