   735→  [#2126](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2126)
   737→## mdBook 0.4.31
   738→[v0.4.30...v0.4.31](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/v0.4.30...v0.4.31)
   740→### Fixed
   741→- Fixed menu border render flash during page navigation.
   742→  [#2101](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2101)
   743→- Fixed flicker setting sidebar scroll position.
   744→  [#2104](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2104)
   745→- Fixed compile error with proc-macro2 on latest Rust nightly.
   746→  [#2109](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2109)
   748→## mdBook 0.4.30
   749→[v0.4.29...v0.4.30](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/v0.4.29...v0.4.30)
   751→### Added
   752→- Added support for heading attributes.
   753→  Attributes are specified in curly braces just after the heading text.
   754→  An HTML ID can be specified with `#` and classes with `.`.
   755→  For example: `## My heading {#custom-id .class1 .class2}`
   756→  [#2013](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2013)
   757→- Added support for hidden code lines for languages other than Rust.
   758→  The `output.html.code.hidelines` table allows you to define the prefix character that will be used to hide code lines based on the language.
   759→  [#2093](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2093)
   761→### Fixed
   762→- Fixed a few minor markdown rendering issues.
   763→  [#2092](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2092)
   765→## mdBook 0.4.29
   766→[v0.4.28...v0.4.29](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/v0.4.28...v0.4.29)
   768→### Changed
   769→- Built-in fonts are no longer copied when `fonts/fonts.css` is overridden in the theme directory.
   770→  Additionally, the warning about `copy-fonts` has been removed if `fonts/fonts.css` is specified.
   771→  [#2080](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2080)
   772→- `mdbook init --force` now skips all interactive prompts as intended.
   773→  [#2057](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/2057)
   774→- Updated dependencies
