  1215→### Fixed
  1216→- Fixed SUMMARY links that contained newlines.
  1217→  [#1291](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1291)
  1218→- Fixed SUMMARY links that contain `%20` spaces.
  1219→  [#1293](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1293)
  1220→- Fixed favicon so that if only the png or svg is overridden, the other is not
  1221→  automatically included in the `<link>` tag.
  1222→  [#1272](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1272)
  1224→## mdBook 0.4.1
  1225→[d4df7e7...649f355](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/d4df7e7...649f355)
  1227→### Changed
  1228→- Removed several outdated dev-dependencies.
  1229→  [#1267](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1267)
  1231→### Fixed
  1232→- Fixed sidebar scrolling if the book includes part titles.
  1233→  [#1265](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1265)
  1234→- Don't include the default favicon if only one of the PNG or SVG is overridden.
  1235→  [#1266](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1266)
  1237→## mdBook 0.4.0
  1238→[99ecd4f...d4df7e7](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/99ecd4f...d4df7e7)
  1240→### Breaking Changes
  1241→- Several of the changes in the release have altered the public API of the
  1242→  mdbook library.
  1243→- Many dependencies have been updated or replaced.
  1244→  This also removes the `--websocket-hostname` and `--websocket-port` from
  1245→  the `serve` command.
  1246→  [#1211](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1211)
  1247→- A new "404" page is now automatically rendered. This requires knowledge of
  1248→  the base URL of your site to work properly. If you decide to use this as
  1249→  your 404 page, you should set the `site-url` setting in the book
  1250→  configuration so mdbook can generate the links correctly. Alternatively you
  1251→  can disable the 404 page generation, or set up your own 404 handling in your
  1252→  web server.
  1253→  [#1221](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1221)
  1254→- The `debug` and `output` features have been removed as they were unused.
  1255→  [#1211](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1211)
  1256→- If you are using customized themes, you may want to consider setting the
  1257→  `preferred-dark-theme` config setting, as it now defaults to "navy".
  1258→  [#1199](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1199)
  1259→- "Playpen" has been renamed to "playground". This is generally backwards
  1260→  compatible for users, but `{{#playpen}}` will now display warnings. This may
  1261→  impact books that have modified the "playpen" elements in the theme.
  1262→  [#1241](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1241)
  1263→- If a renderer is not installed, it is now treated as an error. If you want
  1264→  the old behavior of ignoring missing renderers, set the `optional` setting
  1265→  for that renderer.
  1266→  [#1122](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1122)
  1267→- If you have a custom favicon, you may need to look into adding an SVG
  1268→  version, otherwise the default SVG icon will be displayed.
  1269→  [#1230](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1230)
  1271→### Added
  1272→- Added a new `[rust]` configuration section to `book.toml`, which allows
  1273→  setting the default edition with `edition = "2018"`.
  1274→  [#1163](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1163)
  1275→- Renderers can now be marked as `optional`, so that they will be ignored if
  1276→  the renderer is not installed.
  1277→  [#1122](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1122)
  1278→- Added `head.hbs` to allow adding content to the `<head>` section in HTML.
  1279→  [#1206](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1206)
  1280→- Added "draft chapters". These are chapters listed without a link to indicate
  1281→  content yet to be written.
  1282→  [#1153](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1153)
  1283→- Added "parts" to split a book into different sections. Headers can be added
  1284→  to `SUMMARY.md` to signify different sections.
  1285→  [#1171](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1171)
  1286→- Added generation of a "404" page for handling missing pages and broken links.
  1287→  [#1221](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1221)
  1288→- Added configuration section for specifying URL redirects.
  1289→  [#1237](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1237)
  1290→- Added an SVG favicon that works with light and dark colors schemes.
  1291→  [#1230](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1230)
  1293→### Changed
  1294→- Changed default Rust attribute of `allow(unused_variables)` to `allow(unused)`.
  1295→  [#1195](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1195)
  1296→- Fonts are now served locally instead of from the Google Fonts CDN. The
  1297→  `copy-fonts` option was added to disable this if you want to supply your own
  1298→  fonts.
  1299→  [#1188](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1188)
  1300→- Switched the built-in webserver for the `serve` command to a new
  1301→  implementation. This results in some internal differences in how websockets
  1302→  are handled, which removes the separate websocket options. This should also
  1303→  make it easier to serve multiple books at once.
  1304→  [#1211](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1211)
  1305→- The default dark theme is now "navy".
  1306→  [#1199](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1199)
  1307→- "Playpen" has been renamed to "playground", matching the actual name of the
  1308→  service which was renamed many years ago.
  1309→  [#1241](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1241)
  1311→### Fixed
  1312→- Links with the `+` symbol should now work.
  1313→  [#1208](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1208)
  1314→- The `MDBOOK_BOOK` environment variable now correctly allows overriding the
  1315→  entire book configuration.
  1316→  [#1207](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1207)
  1317→- The sidebar can no longer be dragged outside of the window.
  1318→  [#1229](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1229)
  1319→- Hide the Rust Playground "play" button for `no_run` code samples.
  1320→  [#1249](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1249)
  1321→- Fixed the `--dest-dir` command-line option for the `serve` and `watch`
  1322→  commands.
  1323→  [#1228](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1228)
  1324→- Hotkey handlers are now disabled in `text` input fields (for example, typing
  1325→  `S` in a custom text input field).
  1326→  [#1244](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1244)
  1328→## mdBook 0.3.7
  1329→[88684d8...99ecd4f](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/88684d8...99ecd4f)
  1331→### Changed
  1332→- Code spans in headers are no longer highlighted as code.
  1333→  [#1162](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1162)
  1334→- The sidebar will now scroll the activate page to the middle instead of the top.
  1335→  [#1161](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1161)
  1336→- Reverted change to reject build output within the `src` directory, and
  1337→  instead add a check that prevents infinite copies.
  1338→  [#1181](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1181)
  1339→  [#1026](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1026)
  1341→### Fixed
  1342→- Fixed sidebar line-height jumping for collapsed chapters.
  1343→  [#1182](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1182)
  1344→- Fixed theme selector focus.
  1345→  [#1170](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1170)
  1347→## mdBook 0.3.6
  1348→[efdb832...88684d8](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/efdb832...88684d8)
  1350→### Added
  1351→- `MDBook::execute_build_process` is now publicly accessible in the API so
