  1420→## mdBook 0.3.2
  1421→[9cd47eb...2b649fe](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/9cd47eb...2b649fe)
  1423→### Added
  1424→- Added a markdown renderer, which is off by default. This may be useful for
  1425→  debugging preprocessors.
  1426→  [#1018](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1018)
  1427→- Code samples may now include line numbers with the
  1428→  `output.html.playpen.line-numbers` configuration value.
  1429→  [#1035](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1035)
  1430→- The `watch` and `serve` commands will now ignore files listed in
  1431→  `.gitignore`.
  1432→  [#1044](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1044)
  1433→- Added automatic dark-theme detection based on the CSS `prefers-color-scheme`
  1434→  feature. This may be enabled by setting `output.html.preferred-dark-theme`
  1435→  to your preferred dark theme.
  1436→  [#1037](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1037)
  1437→- Added `rustdoc_include` preprocessor. This makes it easier to include
  1438→  portions of an external Rust source file. The rest of the file is hidden,
  1439→  but the user may expand it to see the entire file, and will continue to work
  1440→  with `mdbook test`.
  1441→  [#1003](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1003)
  1442→- Added Ctrl-Enter shortcut to the playpen editor to automatically run the
  1443→  sample.
  1444→  [#1066](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1066)
  1445→- Added `output.html.playpen.copyable` configuration option to disable
  1446→  the copy button.
  1447→  [#1050](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1050)
  1448→- Added ability to dynamically expand and fold sections within the sidebar.
  1449→  See the `output.html.fold` configuration to enable this feature.
  1450→  [#1027](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1027)
  1452→### Changed
  1453→- Use standard `scrollbar-color` CSS along with webkit extension
  1454→  [#816](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/816)
  1455→- The renderer build directory is no longer deleted before the renderer is
  1456→  run. This allows a backend to cache results between runs.
  1457→  [#985](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/985)
  1458→- Next/prev links now highlight on hover to indicate it is clickable.
  1459→  [#994](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/994)
  1460→- Increase padding of table headers.
  1461→  [#824](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/824)
  1462→- Errors in `[output.html]` config are no longer ignored.
  1463→  [#1033](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1033)
  1464→- Updated highlight.js for syntax highlighting updates (primarily to add
  1465→  async/await to Rust highlighting).
  1466→  [#1041](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1041)
  1467→- Raised minimum supported rust version to 1.35.
  1468→  [#1003](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1003)
  1469→- Hidden code lines are no longer dynamically removed via JavaScript, but
  1470→  instead managed with CSS.
  1471→  [#846](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/846)
  1472→  [#1065](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1065)
  1473→- Changed the default font set for the ACE editor, giving preference to
  1474→  "Source Code Pro".
  1475→  [#1062](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1062)
  1476→- Windows 32-bit releases are no longer published.
  1477→  [#1071](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1071)
  1479→### Fixed
  1480→- Fixed sidebar auto-scrolling.
  1481→  [#1052](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1052)
  1482→- Fixed error message when running `clean` multiple times.
  1483→  [#1055](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/1055)
  1484→- Actually fix the "next" link on index.html. The previous fix didn't work.
