  1613→  for more.
  1614→  [#792](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/792)
  1639→### Fixed
  1640→- Fix paths to additional CSS and JavaScript files
  1641→  [#777](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/777)
  1642→- Ensure section numbers are correctly incremented after a horizontal
  1643→  separator
  1644→  [#790](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/790)
  1646→## mdBook 0.2.1 (2018-08-22)
  1647→[91ffca1...7e2e095](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/compare/91ffca1...7e2e095)
  1649→### Changed
  1650→- Update to handlebars-rs 1.0
  1651→  [#761](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/761)
  1653→### Fixed
  1654→- Fix table colors, broken by Stylus -> CSS transition
  1655→  [#765](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/765)
  1657→## mdBook 0.2.0 (2018-08-02)
  1658→
  1659→### Changed
  1660→- 💥 This release changes how links are handled in mdBook. Previously, relative
  1661→  links were interpreted relative to the book's root. In `0.2.0`+ links are
  1662→  relative to the page they are in, and use the `.md` extension. This has [several
  1663→  advantages](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/603#issue-166701447),
  1664→  such as making links work in other markdown viewers like GitHub. You will
  1665→  likely have to change links in your book to accommodate this change. For
  1666→  example, a book with this layout:
  1697→### Fixed
  1698→- Escaped includes (`\{{#include file.rs}}`) will now render correctly.
  1699→  [f30ce01](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/commit/f30ce0184d71e342141145472bf816419d30a2c5)
  1700→- `index.html` will now render correctly when the book's first section is
  1701→  inside a subdirectory.
  1702→  [#756](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pull/756)
